title: The Exemplary Novels of Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra
creator: Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra
description: LibriVox recording of The Exemplary Novels of Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra, by Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra. [Translated by Walter K. Kelly] Originally compiled by Cervantes himself in 1613 as a collection of "exemplary" stories, this translated version from 1881 brings these stories to the English reader. Included in the collection are twelve stories selected by Cervantes, including "A Deceitful Marriage," which famously transitions seamlessly and humorously into the "Dialogue Between Scipio and Berganza". (Summary by Tim Ferreira) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B 00-10 (172MB) Download M4B 11-20 (168MB) Download M4B 21-30 (160MB)
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; fiction; humor; short stories
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
These are well-read stories, and for the most part are really good in content as well.

One warning (and spoiler): I was a little put aback by (I think it was) The Force of Blood, in which the girl is raped by a stranger, but falls in love with him and marries him in the end. It will probably be offensive to anyone who has been sexually assaulted.
